author: dlr
msg: * Makefile.in
(swig-java-ext-clean): Worked around a problem in the interaction of
this Makefile with versioned directories in the working copy.  If
a versioned directory is deleted (such as the swig/java/ dir was
by this target), then re-created without its .svn/ sub-dir (such
as by SWIG_DIRS and the mkdir-init target), the svn command-line
client will output an error like the following:
$ svn up
subversion/libsvn_subr/io.c:1377: (apr_err=2)
svn: No such file or directory
svn: svn_io_file_open: can't open `subversion/bindings/swig/java/.svn/lock'
Sander tells me that if the directory is not re-created (by the
Makefile) before trying to use the svn command-line client that the
update command will work, but commands like diff, status, etc. will
not (until the missing WC dir is restorted by an update).
